<h2>Key points</h2>
<ul>
<li>Amblyopia, sometimes called "lazy eye", means a decrease in fine vision or visual acuity. </li>
<li>Amblyopia usually happens in one eye because the brain does not fully develop the vision in that eye. </li>
<li>Children under nine are at the highest risk for amblyopia because their vision is still developing. </li>
<li>Treatment depends on your child's age and the cause of the amblyopia. Your doctor will explain the best treatment for your child. </li>
</ul>
